title: The Autobiography of Sherlock Holmes
description:
The Autobiography of Sherlock Holmes by Sherlock Holmes by Don Libey

Overview: The autobiography of Sherlock Holmes, written by him in 1929, and recently discovered as an unpublished manuscript in a book shop in England by the Editor, Don Libey. In what is, quite possibly, one of the great literary finds of all time, Holmes reveals details previously unknown about his life, his education, his work, and numerous cases that have not been revealed before. Essential reading for Sherlockians and Holmesians worldwide
